Thanks. This output clearly identifies the problem.

Root Cause 1 (Primary): Missing SR-IOV resource

Your pod requests:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3: 1

Your NAD also references:

k8s.v1.cni.cncf.io/resourceName: openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

However, your node advertises only:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_1
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2_1

There is NO:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

So the scheduler is correct:

Insufficient openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

That resource does not exist on the node.


---

Root Cause 2: No SR-IOV policy for bh0u_3

Your policies are:

policy-ens1f0-bh0u
policy-ens3f3-bh0u-1
policy-ens4f0-bh0u-2
policy-ens6f0-bh0u-2-1

There is no policy for bh0u_3.

Yet you created:

bscf-bh0u-3-nad

This is an inconsistency.

A NetworkAttachmentDefinition alone does not create SR-IOV resources. It only consumes resources exposed by an existing SR-IOV policy.


---

Root Cause 3: CPU/HugePages

Even if you fixed the SR-IOV resource, your node currently has:

CPU Requests = 80%

HugePages Requests = 16Gi/18Gi


Your pod requests:

CPU = 26
HugePages = 8Gi

Only about 2 GiB of hugepages remain available, so the scheduler will also reject the pod because of hugepage exhaustion.


---

Why networknodestate is missing

You ran:

oc get networknodestate

The correct resource name is:

oc get sriovnetworknodestate -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

or

oc get sriovnetworknodestates -n openshift-sriov-network-operator


---

What to verify next

Run these commands:

oc get sriovnetwork -A

oc get sriovnetworknodestate -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

oc describe sriovnetworknodepolicy policy-ens6f0-bh0u-2-1

oc describe sriovnetworknodepolicy policy-ens4f0-bh0u-2

Also check whether bh0u_3 is expected to be another physical port or whether the application YAML mistakenly references bh0u_3 instead of one of the existing resources (bh0u, bh0u_1, bh0u_2, or bh0u_2_1).

Conclusion

Based on the outputs you provided, the deployment has a configuration mismatch:

❌ The pod requests openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3.

❌ The node does not advertise openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3.

❌ There is no SriovNetworkNodePolicy for bh0u_3.

❌ The node is also short on hugepages (16 GiB of 18 GiB already allocated), so even after fixing the SR-IOV resource, you may still need to free resources or increase the hugepage allocation.
